{
  "stem": "1568.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in our situation-- this is maybe advantage that we had, and-- and basically otherwise I don't know if I would have survived-- is because we came from a different labor camp.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did not go through any selections.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We just got off the train and put into the camp directly.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We just marched into the camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was not a question of selection, not a question of picking people or-- in any way.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But-- because we were just-- everybody went in there, everybody became numbered and got a place to-- to stay.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never heard about Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Never heard about any of the situation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Blizyn, again, I don't-- I don't think that anybody was aware of it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, you used to hear the stories of the Germans put you to-- to work camp, and you join the work.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this is what you were hoping for.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And maybe I'll backtrack a little bit, because going back, when the Germans was out there in the beginning, 1939, my dad used to say, well, he lived through World War I, and he was occupied by the Germans, and they were not terrific, but you were able to live.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You were able to survive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You were able to think.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was never in their mind, in-- in any way, what could possibly happen [? to ?] [? you ?].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we definitely did not-- when we came to Auschwitz, I-- I did not know of any situation, did not have any inkling what is going to happen to me.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And again, it is-- of course, I was a boy of 16 who is supposed to be mature, but you have to understand that war broke out 11.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
